1
00:01:33,156 --> 00:01:34,697
[screaming]

2
00:01:34,777 --> 00:01:36,659
Martial Art,
Swallow's Approach!

3
00:01:38,201 --> 00:01:39,993
[grunting]

4
00:01:40,994 --> 00:01:42,455
-[sword slashing]
-[grunting]

5
00:01:45,459 --> 00:01:46,460
[gasps] Van!

6
00:01:47,421 --> 00:01:49,293
Stay out of this, Lavender.

7
00:01:51,385 --> 00:01:53,047
Foolish girl.

8
00:01:53,137 --> 00:01:54,678
[groaning]

9
00:01:54,759 --> 00:01:58,392
♪

10
00:01:58,553 --> 00:02:00,435
[LAVENDER] You're in my way!

11
00:02:00,515 --> 00:02:06,691
♪

12
00:02:07,192 --> 00:02:09,694
I'll kill you!

13
00:02:11,656 --> 00:02:14,660
[screaming]

14
00:02:20,115 --> 00:02:21,667
[screaming]

15
00:02:21,867 --> 00:02:22,868
[swords clanking]

16
00:02:24,830 --> 00:02:26,422
[grunting]

17
00:02:28,965 --> 00:02:32,338
[LAVENDER (DEMON)]
Van. Van!

18
00:02:32,509 --> 00:02:34,130
[electricity crackling]

19
00:02:35,181 --> 00:02:37,434
Such power is beyond
what we feared.

20
00:02:37,934 --> 00:02:40,307
We cannot let her
break free as she is!

21
00:02:40,637 --> 00:02:42,189
So we must end this here!

22
00:02:42,559 --> 00:02:45,392
[electricity crackling]

23
00:02:45,562 --> 00:02:48,315
[rumbling]

24
00:02:50,398 --> 00:02:53,401
[grunting]

25
00:02:54,862 --> 00:02:56,324
[swords clanking]

26
00:02:57,285 --> 00:02:58,907
[VAN] Lightning of Judgment!

27
00:02:58,997 --> 00:03:00,038
[grunts]

28
00:03:01,409 --> 00:03:02,540
[thumps]

29
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:05,664
[LAVENDER (DEMON)]
Don't touch him!

30
00:03:05,754 --> 00:03:07,215
[RUTI] Sacred Shield.

31
00:03:08,126 --> 00:03:15,134
♪

32
00:03:17,306 --> 00:03:20,309
[screaming]

33
00:03:27,146 --> 00:03:32,402
Martial Art, Great Whirlwind!

34
00:03:32,652 --> 00:03:35,655
[wind gusting]

35
00:03:38,909 --> 00:03:41,201
-[grunting]
-[sword shatters]

36
00:03:41,332 --> 00:03:44,255
♪

37
00:03:44,335 --> 00:03:46,207
[shattering]

38
00:03:46,417 --> 00:03:51,012
♪

39
00:03:53,174 --> 00:03:54,265
[thudding]

40
00:03:56,638 --> 00:03:57,639
[metal clanging]

41
00:04:08,901 --> 00:04:10,442
Victory is mine!

42
00:04:10,823 --> 00:04:13,486
Healing Hands Mastery:
Reflection!

43
00:04:13,866 --> 00:04:14,867
[chuckles]

44
00:04:16,829 --> 00:04:18,201
Sure took you long enough.

45
00:04:18,411 --> 00:04:22,245
♪

46
00:04:22,705 --> 00:04:23,706
[gasps]

47
00:04:23,877 --> 00:04:24,958
-[slashing]
-[grunts]

48
00:04:25,669 --> 00:04:28,672
[groaning]

49
00:04:29,002 --> 00:04:30,093
[thuds]

50
00:04:31,054 --> 00:04:32,596
[coin clinking]

51
00:04:33,887 --> 00:04:35,309
Never call it early.

52
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:39,393
You held the power of the Hero?

53
00:04:40,434 --> 00:04:41,435
Yeah.

54
00:04:41,645 --> 00:04:44,569
Ruti infused the ornament
right before our duel.

55
00:04:44,899 --> 00:04:47,772
Face the facts, Van,
ultimate skills can cancel

56
00:04:47,862 --> 00:04:48,863
each other out.

57
00:04:48,943 --> 00:04:52,327
♪

58
00:04:52,447 --> 00:04:53,488
Deceit.

59
00:04:54,579 --> 00:04:58,083
Wrong, you're fundamentally
mistaken there, Van.

60
00:05:00,085 --> 00:05:01,707
[RED] On the surface,
you might have thought

61
00:05:01,787 --> 00:05:03,959
this was a duel
between Guide and Hero.

62
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:05,501
But take all of that away,

63
00:05:05,591 --> 00:05:07,543
and this was a fight
between two men.

64
00:05:07,843 --> 00:05:10,546
Blessings alone weren't enough
to decide the outcome.

65
00:05:10,716 --> 00:05:13,219
That's a small part
of what makes us who we are.

66
00:05:13,719 --> 00:05:14,761
[trembling]

67
00:05:15,221 --> 00:05:17,724
-Damn you.
-Embrace it, Van.

68
00:05:18,014 --> 00:05:20,477
It was that emotion
that was making you waver.

69
00:05:20,807 --> 00:05:21,938
You get it now?

70
00:05:22,269 --> 00:05:23,270
[gasps]

71
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:25,192
Think back
to our mission together.

72
00:05:25,562 --> 00:05:27,945
Didn't it feel like
you lost to me somehow?

73
00:05:28,866 --> 00:05:30,617
You knew the kid
would have been a goner

74
00:05:30,697 --> 00:05:31,699
without our help.

75
00:05:31,779 --> 00:05:33,781
Because of your pride,
you felt undeserving

76
00:05:33,871 --> 00:05:35,573
of the gratitude
she showed you.

77
00:05:36,704 --> 00:05:38,326
For the first time
in your life,

78
00:05:38,666 --> 00:05:40,828
you felt what
we call disappointment.

79
00:05:41,379 --> 00:05:43,831
It feels...heavy.

80
00:05:45,753 --> 00:05:48,546
Sure does,
now get some rest.

81
00:05:48,967 --> 00:05:50,258
And we'll talk later.

82
00:05:59,558 --> 00:06:01,520
[LAVENDER] Van, wake up!

83
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,023
Open your eyes, please!

84
00:06:04,193 --> 00:06:06,656
[groaning]

85
00:06:08,027 --> 00:06:09,238
[LAVENDER] Van!

86
00:06:10,029 --> 00:06:11,240
[VAN] Lavender.

87
00:06:13,072 --> 00:06:14,284
Where are we?

88
00:06:17,327 --> 00:06:19,499
[door slides opens]

89
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:22,252
-Hey! Sleepyhead.
-[groans]

90
00:06:22,753 --> 00:06:23,924
Sleepy-what?

91
00:06:24,124 --> 00:06:26,627
Release me this instant,
you good for nothing bum!

92
00:06:26,837 --> 00:06:28,509
Can't you see Van needs me?

93
00:06:28,799 --> 00:06:30,801
A curse on you
for keeping us apart!

94
00:06:31,011 --> 00:06:32,933
[grunting]

95
00:06:33,935 --> 00:06:35,977
Keeping you from going
berserk, you mean.

96
00:06:36,057 --> 00:06:38,810
Now just pipe down and deal
with it for a bit, okay?

97
00:06:38,890 --> 00:06:41,483
[growling]
I'll deal with you, all right!

98
00:06:41,693 --> 00:06:43,855
Desperate times
call for magical mending.

99
00:06:44,646 --> 00:06:45,697
How do you feel?

100
00:06:46,738 --> 00:06:48,200
Far less than heroic.

101
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:50,862
Sure does suck getting
your tail handed to you

102
00:06:50,953 --> 00:06:52,574
by your sworn nemesis.

103
00:06:53,245 --> 00:06:55,077
Is that your attempt
to humiliate me?

104
00:06:55,457 --> 00:06:56,999
-[Red chuckles]
-[gasps]

105
00:06:57,620 --> 00:06:58,661
[grunts] Tell me.

106
00:06:58,831 --> 00:07:00,543
What became
of Albert and Ljubo?

107
00:07:01,123 --> 00:07:02,715
Recovering from their wounds.

108
00:07:03,045 --> 00:07:04,757
Albert's regained
consciousness,

109
00:07:05,218 --> 00:07:07,010
while Cardinal Ljubo
is laid up in bed.

110
00:07:07,090 --> 00:07:08,171
[LAVENDER] Curses!

111
00:07:08,421 --> 00:07:10,633
[RED] Took a while before he
was treated for his injuries,

112
00:07:10,724 --> 00:07:12,636
so he'll definitely
need more rest.

113
00:07:14,978 --> 00:07:16,640
[sighs] Because of me.

114
00:07:20,734 --> 00:07:22,066
[groans]

115
00:07:24,278 --> 00:07:25,279
[gasps]

116
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:27,361
What now, princess?

117
00:07:27,441 --> 00:07:29,403
I Think some fresh air
will do us good.

118
00:07:29,573 --> 00:07:31,946
Guides and Heroes only, sorry.

119
00:07:32,036 --> 00:07:34,198
Hurt Van again,
and it's over for you, bum!

120
00:07:34,329 --> 00:07:36,291
As in, goodnight forever!

121
00:07:36,371 --> 00:07:38,002
So say your prayers!

122
00:07:39,294 --> 00:07:40,295
You hear me?

123
00:07:41,046 --> 00:07:42,127
Say something!

124
00:07:42,207 --> 00:07:43,378
[door closes]

125
00:07:46,211 --> 00:07:47,262
[RED] How's your Blessing?

126
00:07:47,963 --> 00:07:49,384
[VAN] It has returned to me.

127
00:07:50,095 --> 00:07:52,137
I can feel
the impulse once more.

128
00:07:53,269 --> 00:07:55,561
I have no desire
to see another in pain.

129
00:07:56,472 --> 00:07:57,473
Good to hear.

130
00:07:58,104 --> 00:07:59,105
[knife clinks]

131
00:08:00,276 --> 00:08:03,980
♪

132
00:08:06,573 --> 00:08:08,365
Considering you went
through some pretty heavy

133
00:08:08,445 --> 00:08:09,866
emotional turmoil,

134
00:08:10,157 --> 00:08:12,199
it must've made your Blessing
go berserk.

135
00:08:13,910 --> 00:08:15,542
Turmoil? I see.

136
00:08:15,702 --> 00:08:18,085
♪

137
00:08:18,165 --> 00:08:21,168
Perhaps, disappointment
was a stranger to me

138
00:08:21,248 --> 00:08:22,460
for so long.

139
00:08:24,001 --> 00:08:26,674
[VAN] Am I now
unfit to be a Hero?

140
00:08:26,754 --> 00:08:30,508
♪

141
00:08:30,678 --> 00:08:34,933
[RED] Van, a Blessing by itself
doesn't turn you into the Hero.

142
00:08:36,104 --> 00:08:38,226
Don't go around saying
you're the Hero,

143
00:08:38,316 --> 00:08:39,438
act like one.

144
00:08:39,898 --> 00:08:41,320
I do not understand.

145
00:08:41,860 --> 00:08:45,654
Asking yourself what it means
to support and protect others.

146
00:08:45,824 --> 00:08:47,907
Listening to guidance
when offered.

147
00:08:48,737 --> 00:08:50,239
Wavering and worrying...

148
00:08:51,490 --> 00:08:54,203
and yet always striving
to be a better person.

149
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:57,286
That's a Hero in my eyes.

150
00:08:57,497 --> 00:09:04,294
♪

151
00:09:04,674 --> 00:09:08,298
So then...what is my role?

152
00:09:10,761 --> 00:09:12,142
Good question!

153
00:09:13,013 --> 00:09:15,936
I'll be honest with you,
you're one ignorant guy.

154
00:09:16,477 --> 00:09:19,270
You lack perspective,
and your sword's sorry.

155
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,651
Hey, I reject that!

156
00:09:20,731 --> 00:09:23,985
Name one strategy you have
that isn't brute force.

157
00:09:24,195 --> 00:09:26,157
One counter,
and you hit the ground!

158
00:09:26,527 --> 00:09:27,529
[gasps]

159
00:09:27,619 --> 00:09:28,620
[groans]

160
00:09:29,661 --> 00:09:31,122
-[RED] Keep it up.
-Huh?

161
00:09:32,494 --> 00:09:33,785
Don't change a thing.

162
00:09:34,706 --> 00:09:37,249
Understand your emotions
and accept that you're human,

163
00:09:37,329 --> 00:09:38,750
first and foremost.

164
00:09:39,251 --> 00:09:41,043
That might make you
weaker in the moment.

165
00:09:41,543 --> 00:09:43,085
But trusting your friends...

166
00:09:43,335 --> 00:09:45,257
that gives purpose
to your sword.

167
00:09:45,428 --> 00:09:47,139
Strength will return to you.

168
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:51,013
And that is when
you will be the truest Hero.

169
00:09:52,645 --> 00:09:54,767
The truest Hero.

170
00:09:55,688 --> 00:09:58,481
[RED] First off,
try listening to Esta's advice.

171
00:09:58,942 --> 00:10:01,064
Talk to her about anything
on your mind,

172
00:10:01,485 --> 00:10:03,156
not just about being a hero.

173
00:10:03,987 --> 00:10:05,359
[VAN] After all I've done,

174
00:10:05,489 --> 00:10:08,412
would she welcome me once more
as a travel companion?

175
00:10:08,993 --> 00:10:11,325
So long as you desire
to be the Hero,

176
00:10:11,495 --> 00:10:13,367
and learn from your mistakes,

177
00:10:13,748 --> 00:10:16,040
you can lean on her
as your personal guide.

178
00:10:17,622 --> 00:10:18,713
My guide?

179
00:10:19,293 --> 00:10:22,427
She may not have the Blessing,
but that doesn't stop her

180
00:10:22,507 --> 00:10:23,838
from looking after you.

181
00:10:24,429 --> 00:10:27,092
And believe it or not,
no one in their right mind

182
00:10:27,182 --> 00:10:28,934
would cast their lot
with a brat like you

183
00:10:29,014 --> 00:10:30,055
if they didn't care.

184
00:10:30,185 --> 00:10:31,186
Huh.

185
00:10:31,807 --> 00:10:32,808
[gasps]

186
00:10:34,139 --> 00:10:36,101
[sighs]
Wicked thing to say.

187
00:10:37,313 --> 00:10:39,695
And yet, I do deserve it.

188
00:10:39,895 --> 00:10:45,111
♪

189
00:10:45,321 --> 00:10:46,532
Say, Gideon.

190
00:10:47,453 --> 00:10:49,786
Would you join my party
if I asked you to?

191
00:10:49,866 --> 00:10:52,619
Sorry, kiddo,
but I'm already Ruti's Guide.

192
00:10:52,829 --> 00:10:55,212
And I don't plan
on teaming up with a new Hero.

193
00:10:57,124 --> 00:10:58,215
What a shame.

194
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:02,719
If only our paths had crossed
before I awakened.

195
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:08,516
♪

196
00:11:08,726 --> 00:11:09,727
Van...

197
00:11:10,978 --> 00:11:12,770
when did your Blessing change?

198
00:11:13,641 --> 00:11:14,852
How did you know?

199
00:11:15,063 --> 00:11:17,775
While we fought the demonic
army on the battlefield,

200
00:11:17,986 --> 00:11:20,238
you never made
a single appearance there.

201
00:11:21,189 --> 00:11:23,191
Too busy living in a monastery?

202
00:11:24,943 --> 00:11:26,615
Does nothing escape you?

203
00:11:27,616 --> 00:11:29,908
Yes...the change.

204
00:11:30,199 --> 00:11:32,751
Like Ljubo,
I had the Cardinal's Blessing.

205
00:11:33,582 --> 00:11:36,705
Until, one day,
I awakened anew.

206
00:11:38,507 --> 00:11:41,420
I believed it was a miracle
Lord Demis granted me.

207
00:11:42,922 --> 00:11:44,093
I renounced it all.

208
00:11:44,674 --> 00:11:46,676
To embrace my calling as Hero.

209
00:11:48,308 --> 00:11:49,469
I see.

210
00:11:49,889 --> 00:11:51,681
So you had to suddenly
change paths

211
00:11:51,771 --> 00:11:53,774
and lead a completely
different lifestyle.

212
00:11:53,974 --> 00:11:56,316
-That sounds rough.
-Very.

213
00:11:58,188 --> 00:12:00,941
[RED] Your future's bright,
and all in your hands now.

214
00:12:01,282 --> 00:12:04,115
[RED] Are you leaving soon?
[VAN] Of course I... Huh.

215
00:12:04,365 --> 00:12:05,866
Hm. Wait.

216
00:12:07,408 --> 00:12:09,330
On second thought, let me...

217
00:12:10,041 --> 00:12:11,703
consult my party first.

218
00:12:11,793 --> 00:12:16,297
♪

219
00:12:16,458 --> 00:12:17,749
[sighs]

220
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:19,921
-[VAN] Lavender.
-Huh.

221
00:12:20,422 --> 00:12:21,633
[LAVENDER] You're back!

222
00:12:22,504 --> 00:12:24,306
No funny business, right?

223
00:12:24,506 --> 00:12:26,098
Hm, I'm fine.

224
00:12:26,889 --> 00:12:27,890
Really.

225
00:12:28,390 --> 00:12:29,391
[gasps]

226
00:12:29,972 --> 00:12:33,726
Lavender...you've been
faithfully by my side.

227
00:12:34,397 --> 00:12:35,438
Thank you.

228
00:12:35,898 --> 00:12:36,899
Huh.

229
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:38,521
[giggles]

230
00:12:39,822 --> 00:12:40,984
Don't mention it.

231
00:12:41,154 --> 00:12:44,447
♪

232
00:12:46,830 --> 00:12:47,951
[birds chirping]

233
00:12:48,031 --> 00:12:49,122
[knocking on door]

234
00:12:49,743 --> 00:12:50,874
[ESTA] Pardon me.

235
00:12:55,749 --> 00:12:58,422
How do you fare...Cardinal?

236
00:12:58,793 --> 00:13:01,505
[sighs] Hand over
my drinks and cigars,

237
00:13:01,595 --> 00:13:03,217
then ask me how I fare.

238
00:13:03,548 --> 00:13:04,719
[chuckles]

239
00:13:04,889 --> 00:13:06,180
You men of the cloth.

240
00:13:08,142 --> 00:13:09,804
Van visited recently.

241
00:13:09,894 --> 00:13:12,107
Came practically begging
for my forgiveness.

242
00:13:12,687 --> 00:13:15,650
As if that wasn't enough,
he asked me to rejoin him.

243
00:13:15,811 --> 00:13:17,522
[ESTA]
And what was your answer?

244
00:13:17,863 --> 00:13:19,314
Acceptance, of course.

245
00:13:19,404 --> 00:13:22,067
Troublesome as he can be,
no matter his sins,

246
00:13:22,157 --> 00:13:24,410
that boy will save
the world one day.

247
00:13:25,281 --> 00:13:27,373
My divine ambitions made real.

248
00:13:27,493 --> 00:13:29,325
And all I'd need is a Hero.

249
00:13:29,535 --> 00:13:30,626
[chuckles]

250
00:13:30,706 --> 00:13:33,880
Even so, his words
of regret were most surprising.

251
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:37,083
Esta, you surely put him
up to it, didn't you?

252
00:13:37,383 --> 00:13:39,175
No, I did nothing of the sort.

253
00:13:39,636 --> 00:13:41,508
Van's had a true
change of heart.

254
00:13:41,638 --> 00:13:44,341
He seems to be truly remorseful
for what he's done.

255
00:13:45,142 --> 00:13:47,804
He even sought forgiveness
from Albert and the mayor.

256
00:13:47,935 --> 00:13:54,942
♪

257
00:13:55,733 --> 00:13:58,696
[ESTA] Imagine their surprise
to see him bow his head.

258
00:13:59,657 --> 00:14:03,571
All thanks to that Gideon,
a divine addition to our party.

259
00:14:04,162 --> 00:14:06,074
But a man can dream, can't he?

260
00:14:07,325 --> 00:14:08,917
Theodora Dephilo?

261
00:14:10,078 --> 00:14:12,921
-And who might that be?
-[Ljubo chuckles]

262
00:14:13,121 --> 00:14:14,833
[LJUBO] You're a terrible liar.

263
00:14:16,545 --> 00:14:17,796
[kids laughing]

264
00:14:17,876 --> 00:14:19,878
[indistinct chatter]

265
00:14:19,969 --> 00:14:21,630
[FEMALE CHILD]
You're really good at this.

266
00:14:22,882 --> 00:14:24,974
[yawns]

267
00:14:26,435 --> 00:14:27,847
[MALE CHILD 207E]
Sir Eero!

268
00:14:29,849 --> 00:14:32,812
Not another step,
you're scaring them!

269
00:14:32,892 --> 00:14:34,234
What do you want?

270
00:14:34,314 --> 00:14:36,566
♪

271
00:14:36,646 --> 00:14:40,030
Their fear is my fault alone,
forgive me.

272
00:14:40,651 --> 00:14:41,742
Please.

273
00:14:41,822 --> 00:14:43,033
[gasps]

274
00:14:43,534 --> 00:14:46,116
Your home, the lives you live.

275
00:14:46,407 --> 00:14:48,579
If only I'd asked
about that earlier.

276
00:14:50,621 --> 00:14:51,662
Huh.

277
00:14:52,003 --> 00:14:53,794
Come pway wit us, eero!

278
00:14:55,716 --> 00:14:56,718
[chuckles]

279
00:14:57,378 --> 00:14:58,509
[VAN] Sure.

280
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:00,472
[Male Child 207E chuckles] Yay!

281
00:15:00,842 --> 00:15:02,674
-Let's pway, Mister Eero!
-Huh?

282
00:15:03,425 --> 00:15:05,887
[all laughing]

283
00:15:06,428 --> 00:15:08,390
[TANTA] All right,
whose turn is it again?

284
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:10,272
[indistinct chatter]

285
00:15:11,273 --> 00:15:13,355
[LAVENDER]
Ugh, this is torture!

286
00:15:13,525 --> 00:15:15,608
Someone tell me
why Van has to go around

287
00:15:15,688 --> 00:15:17,440
apologizing to people?

288
00:15:17,690 --> 00:15:20,323
I mean, this was his idea,
Lavender.

289
00:15:20,653 --> 00:15:22,535
Sure, but it's like
watching my darling

290
00:15:22,615 --> 00:15:25,288
become a totally different
person before my eyes!

291
00:15:27,290 --> 00:15:29,202
Are you falling
out of love with him?

292
00:15:29,292 --> 00:15:30,623
Don't be ridiculous!

293
00:15:30,704 --> 00:15:32,335
If anything, I love... Huh.

294
00:15:32,586 --> 00:15:34,508
[groans]

295
00:15:34,798 --> 00:15:36,960
This wasn't supposed to happen.

296
00:15:39,343 --> 00:15:41,675
Guess what,
our mead is top notch.

297
00:15:42,096 --> 00:15:43,307
Think booze will cheer you up?

298
00:15:43,387 --> 00:15:46,100
Oh, you bet it will,
bring on the snacks, too!

299
00:15:46,180 --> 00:15:49,143
Atta girl,
libations coming right up!

300
00:15:49,644 --> 00:15:50,645
[chuckles]

301
00:15:55,860 --> 00:15:58,863
[crickets chirping]

302
00:15:59,824 --> 00:16:00,946
All done.

303
00:16:01,196 --> 00:16:02,237
-[LAVENDER] Hey.
-Huh.

304
00:16:02,908 --> 00:16:05,040
[RED] Oh, hey, what a surprise.

305
00:16:05,871 --> 00:16:08,163
[LAVENDER] Just so you know,
I hate your guts.

306
00:16:08,414 --> 00:16:09,795
And I'll never,
ever forgive you

307
00:16:09,875 --> 00:16:11,707
for raising your sword
to Van, got it?

308
00:16:12,087 --> 00:16:14,340
Well, he cut me first,
so we're even now.

309
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:16,092
[blowing raspberries]

310
00:16:16,592 --> 00:16:18,384
-Take this!
-[grunts]

311
00:16:19,055 --> 00:16:20,096
[sighs]

312
00:16:20,637 --> 00:16:21,638
Huh.

313
00:16:21,968 --> 00:16:22,969
Hm.

314
00:16:23,510 --> 00:16:24,931
Wait, is this...

315
00:16:26,102 --> 00:16:27,314
a blue sapphire?

316
00:16:27,934 --> 00:16:29,976
As thanks
for looking after Van.

317
00:16:30,067 --> 00:16:31,148
Huh.

318
00:16:31,688 --> 00:16:34,191
[RED] How did you find this?

319
00:16:34,521 --> 00:16:36,233
[LAVENDER]
Rit and I had some drinks,

320
00:16:36,483 --> 00:16:38,576
and she mentioned
her good-for-nothing lover

321
00:16:38,656 --> 00:16:40,778
needed some rock
for an engagement ring.

322
00:16:41,078 --> 00:16:43,701
I could get my hands on gold
if I asked the fairies,

323
00:16:43,781 --> 00:16:45,453
but if it's what you want.

324
00:16:45,743 --> 00:16:47,285
How do you archfay do it?

325
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:49,878
Find the answer
at my altar, boy.

326
00:16:50,538 --> 00:16:51,539
Sure, sure.

327
00:16:51,629 --> 00:16:53,752
[scoffs]
Don't screw this up!

328
00:16:54,002 --> 00:16:56,715
♪

329
00:16:56,885 --> 00:16:57,886
[RIT] Huh?

330
00:16:57,966 --> 00:17:00,849
[RIT] Where is that fairy?
[LAVENDER] Waiting for you!

331
00:17:01,009 --> 00:17:02,261
[LAVENDER] Let's get drinking!

332
00:17:02,431 --> 00:17:04,103
[RIT]
Someone's in a better mood!

333
00:17:04,303 --> 00:17:06,645
♪

334
00:17:06,765 --> 00:17:07,766
[sighs]

335
00:17:08,477 --> 00:17:09,478
Hm.

336
00:17:10,690 --> 00:17:11,731
[MOGRIM] Aw!

337
00:17:13,443 --> 00:17:15,024
Seen my fair share
of sapphires,

338
00:17:15,114 --> 00:17:17,317
but this one sure
takes the prize.

339
00:17:17,617 --> 00:17:20,320
Her ring will sparkle like
the moonlight with this rock!

340
00:17:20,410 --> 00:17:22,282
[RED] Really? [chuckles]

341
00:17:22,452 --> 00:17:24,664
[MOGRIM] Not in a rush, right?
[RED] Nope.

342
00:17:25,075 --> 00:17:26,286
Slide this way, Red.

343
00:17:26,496 --> 00:17:28,579
I'm closin' up shop
for the day.

344
00:17:28,829 --> 00:17:30,461
[Mogrim chuckles] Mink, dear!

345
00:17:31,131 --> 00:17:32,923
Get my jeweler's tools for me!

346
00:17:33,424 --> 00:17:34,925
Er, no, no, never mind!

347
00:17:35,426 --> 00:17:36,717
Stay put, I got it!

348
00:17:37,088 --> 00:17:39,050
What are you doing, pal,
don't be shy now!

349
00:17:39,140 --> 00:17:40,221
[chuckles]

350
00:17:41,052 --> 00:17:48,059
♪

351
00:17:52,814 --> 00:17:55,817
[crickets chirping]

352
00:17:57,199 --> 00:17:59,281
[crackling]

353
00:18:04,166 --> 00:18:05,167
There.

354
00:18:08,421 --> 00:18:10,793
Hey, Rit,
come on down for dinner!

355
00:18:11,504 --> 00:18:12,505
[RIT] Okay!

356
00:18:17,470 --> 00:18:19,342
[door opens and closes]

357
00:18:25,849 --> 00:18:26,850
[sighs]

358
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:28,983
[RIT] Oh?

359
00:18:29,523 --> 00:18:31,816
Did I miss an important date
or something?

360
00:18:32,276 --> 00:18:34,198
You didn't, don't worry, Rit.

361
00:18:35,149 --> 00:18:36,150
Huh?

362
00:18:39,113 --> 00:18:40,114
Hm.

363
00:18:42,957 --> 00:18:44,039
[clearing throat]

364
00:18:44,369 --> 00:18:45,961
There's something
I wanna give you.

365
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:47,042
[gasps]

366
00:18:50,756 --> 00:18:51,837
[Rit gasps]

367
00:18:52,668 --> 00:18:54,299
[RIT] Is that a blue sapphire?

368
00:18:56,091 --> 00:18:57,553
No, you didn't, Red.

369
00:18:57,923 --> 00:18:59,305
-Listen!
-I'm listening?

370
00:18:59,925 --> 00:19:02,058
If you don't mind, could you...

371
00:19:03,139 --> 00:19:04,140
[gulps]

372
00:19:05,772 --> 00:19:06,773
No.

373
00:19:07,984 --> 00:19:09,025
I mean.

374
00:19:09,105 --> 00:19:10,106
Huh?

375
00:19:14,070 --> 00:19:15,152
My love.

376
00:19:16,743 --> 00:19:18,405
May I have your hand
in marriage?

377
00:19:18,825 --> 00:19:19,907
[gasps]

378
00:19:20,287 --> 00:19:21,288
[RIT] Red.

379
00:19:22,039 --> 00:19:23,540
I'm in love with you, Rit.

380
00:19:24,702 --> 00:19:26,584
From the moment
I first saw you,

381
00:19:27,084 --> 00:19:28,836
that fateful day in Loggervia.

382
00:19:28,956 --> 00:19:35,964
♪

383
00:19:38,676 --> 00:19:40,889
Even though
I may not be the hero,

384
00:19:41,059 --> 00:19:42,851
and I'm far
from the knights or kings

385
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:45,604
that princesses deserve...
Rizlet.

386
00:19:46,104 --> 00:19:48,227
I promise to make you
the happiest woman.

387
00:19:48,777 --> 00:19:51,981
And promise to make you
breakfast every morning

388
00:19:52,071 --> 00:19:53,192
until the day I die.

389
00:19:53,903 --> 00:19:55,614
Nothing would make me happier.

390
00:19:55,735 --> 00:19:56,786
[crying]

391
00:19:56,986 --> 00:19:57,987
Hm.

392
00:19:59,038 --> 00:20:02,662
♪

393
00:20:02,792 --> 00:20:04,794
[RIT] I should be
the one asking you.

394
00:20:05,545 --> 00:20:08,298
Darling, would you
please marry me?

395
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:12,673
Marry me because
my heart belongs to you.

396
00:20:13,674 --> 00:20:15,636
Because even
when we grow into old

397
00:20:15,716 --> 00:20:17,347
and wrinkly grandparents,

398
00:20:18,058 --> 00:20:20,010
spending the rest
of my life with you

399
00:20:20,100 --> 00:20:21,762
is all I can ever ask for.

400
00:20:22,513 --> 00:20:23,514
[RED] Rit.

401
00:20:23,684 --> 00:20:29,070
♪

402
00:20:29,771 --> 00:20:30,772
[chuckles]

403
00:20:30,942 --> 00:20:36,738
♪

404
00:20:36,948 --> 00:20:38,029
[RIT] Pinch me.

405
00:20:39,991 --> 00:20:41,283
Am I dreaming?

406
00:20:41,783 --> 00:20:43,455
[crying]

407
00:20:44,086 --> 00:20:45,167
Red!

408
00:20:45,748 --> 00:20:48,501
♪

409
00:20:48,751 --> 00:20:49,882
[RED] I love you.

410
00:20:51,043 --> 00:20:54,547
♪

411
00:20:56,259 --> 00:21:02,555
♪

412
00:21:02,646 --> 00:21:04,648
[ALL] Congratulations!

413
00:21:05,609 --> 00:21:06,940
-[chuckles]
-Thanks a lot, everyone.

414
00:21:07,020 --> 00:21:08,652
Look at you now, Sir Guide.

415
00:21:09,062 --> 00:21:11,024
Together at last
with your beloved.

416
00:21:11,315 --> 00:21:13,737
Glad I'm in Zoltan
to witness you thrive.

417
00:21:14,118 --> 00:21:15,159
-How kind!
-So are we!

418
00:21:16,370 --> 00:21:17,571
-Rit, dear.
-Huh?

419
00:21:18,032 --> 00:21:20,915
My friend will have a lifetime
of happiness because of you.

420
00:21:21,666 --> 00:21:22,667
So, thanks!

421
00:21:22,747 --> 00:21:24,579
-[munching]
-[Danan gulping]

422
00:21:24,959 --> 00:21:26,921
Who would have thought
that years later,

423
00:21:27,041 --> 00:21:28,633
our friends would be engaged?

424
00:21:29,754 --> 00:21:30,835
People change.

425
00:21:31,426 --> 00:21:33,508
In fact, you've changed
some yourself.

426
00:21:33,718 --> 00:21:34,720
[ESTA] Huh?

427
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:38,554
[chuckles] Any stories you can
share of Esta's former life?

428
00:21:38,684 --> 00:21:39,895
I would love to hear them!

429
00:21:39,975 --> 00:21:41,397
That does sound insightful.

430
00:21:41,597 --> 00:21:43,098
[LAVENDER] Pass!
[DANAN] I'll fill you in.

431
00:21:43,309 --> 00:21:46,021
[YARANDRALA] Apparently, our
Esta saw Ruti and the others

432
00:21:46,102 --> 00:21:47,853
as threats back
when they first met.

433
00:21:48,104 --> 00:21:49,655
[ESTA]
We are not talking about that!

434
00:21:49,735 --> 00:21:51,067
[RUTI] Big Brother.
[ESTA] Albert, tell us more

435
00:21:51,157 --> 00:21:52,278
about yourself instead!

436
00:21:52,739 --> 00:21:54,531
We wanted to congratulate you.

437
00:21:54,781 --> 00:21:56,663
You know...again.

438
00:21:56,953 --> 00:21:58,495
[squeaks]

439
00:21:58,745 --> 00:21:59,616
Tisse.

440
00:22:00,116 --> 00:22:02,669
You two are absolutely
glowing together.

441
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:05,292
It's like a miracle
in front of me.

442
00:22:06,373 --> 00:22:07,584
Oh, Ruti.

443
00:22:07,795 --> 00:22:10,878
All worth it in the end,
to hear that from you.

444
00:22:11,719 --> 00:22:12,720
Yep.

445
00:22:12,840 --> 00:22:14,682
Suppose it's my turn next.

446
00:22:14,972 --> 00:22:16,224
[TISSE] Next?

447
00:22:17,935 --> 00:22:20,308
[DANAN] Come on, the kid
needs more meat than that!

448
00:22:20,478 --> 00:22:22,640
Please don't,
I have no need for entrées!

449
00:22:22,730 --> 00:22:23,731
[ALBERT] Good idea!

450
00:22:23,812 --> 00:22:25,443
[LAVENDER]
Tasty mead, here I come!

451
00:22:25,523 --> 00:22:26,524
[giggles]

452
00:22:26,605 --> 00:22:27,606
[sighs]

453
00:22:28,527 --> 00:22:30,028
Now let's plan mine.

454
00:22:30,198 --> 00:22:32,200
[YARANDRALA] Looks like
you need to hustle, Esta.

455
00:22:32,281 --> 00:22:33,402
[ESTA] Wait. What?

456
00:22:34,533 --> 00:22:36,785
[RED] The Hero's journey
isn't an easy one.

457
00:22:37,866 --> 00:22:39,408
I know that all too well.

458
00:22:40,619 --> 00:22:41,620
Hm.

459
00:22:44,213 --> 00:22:48,298
[RED] But, unlike Ruti,
Van desires not the slow life,

460
00:22:48,378 --> 00:22:49,469
but to fight.

461
00:22:50,420 --> 00:22:52,472
I don't have it in me
to tell him that he's wrong.

462
00:22:52,552 --> 00:22:55,846
♪

463
00:22:55,926 --> 00:22:57,557
[RED] Before he
goes on his way,

464
00:22:58,098 --> 00:22:59,980
I think I'll continue
to play my part

465
00:23:00,060 --> 00:23:02,352
in Van the Hero's story
a bit longer.

466
00:23:02,433 --> 00:23:05,896
♪

467
00:23:06,066 --> 00:23:07,067
[RED] Van.

468
00:23:10,071 --> 00:23:11,692
[wind rustling]

469
00:23:34,767 --> 00:23:37,770
-[wind whooshing]
-[birds chirping]

